# Velocity — MapKit routing & polylines

## Sources of truth

- The SwiftUI map view (`MapScreen`) must render from `MapViewModel` state (`destination`, `currentRoute`, `cameraPosition`).
- Polyline rendering must come from `MKRoute` (`RouteInfo.polylineCoordinates` → `MapPolyline`).

## Route building policy

- Route calculation triggers belong in `MapViewModel` / services (not in SwiftUI view bodies).
- When origin→destination routing fails due to missing/unstable origin, route refresh should recover on later location fixes.
- Live route refresh is throttled/debounced using movement thresholds (distance/time) and generation tokens so MapKit is not spammed.

## Reverse geocoding policy

- Reverse geocoding destination labels should be cached by quantized coordinates (Velocity plan: round to 4 decimal places) to avoid repeated lookups.
- Only geocode on destination commit (set / drag end), not on every drag tick.

## Privacy

- Do not log raw route coordinates or user-derived locations in production logs.

## Active trip integration

- The “active trip” screen should consume a shared route snapshot (from session/store state), not recalculate independently.
